README

The e4thcom program consists of two files, a binary file named e4thcom and an
image file named e4thcom.i. The binary file loads the image file at program
start. 

The binary file and the image file must always have the same name and the image
file must have the .i extension.

e4thcom comes pre-compiled for X86_64 Linux but may be recompiled for X86_32
or Raspbian_32.

To recompile it open a terminal in the e4thcom-x.y.z/src directory and enter
./lxmake 32|64. This creates the 32 or 64 Bit binary and moves it and the 
required image file to the e4thcom-x.y.z directory. gcc warnings concerning 
"unused results" can be ignored.

